summary: This is an email chain from January 2020 regarding the logistical planning and authorization for a U.S. government employee's foreign travel to Sweden, likely related to the Epstein investigation. The correspondence involves coordinating passport retrieval, booking travel through official channels, and obtaining signed travel authorization memos.

events.title: Planned Travel to Sweden
events.description: A trip to Sweden by a U.S. government employee, likely related to the Epstein case, is being planned and pushed back to the week of February 3rd, 2020.

keyFacts: A U.S. government employee's trip to Sweden, likely for the Epstein investigation, was scheduled for the week of February 3, 2020.
The travel required specific booking procedures through an official travel agent (CWT) using fully refundable fares on American carriers.
The process involved obtaining a signed travel authorization memo and coordinating with the Executive Office for United States Attorneys (EOUSA) for passport and itinerary verification.
